This paper deals with the design of modulation schemes for wireless bidirectional relaying, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of Latin Squares in the proposed scheme also involves combinatorial optimization (cs.CC) and mathematical modeling (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of multiple access interference, which is a common issue in wireless communication systems and falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
